      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WHODAT HOOKED (1) put in a much better performance last start when in the placings at Murray Bridge behind Adhana Henry (31.16) in a Grade 6. Has the pace to be prominent. Has performed well from this box with a win and three minor placings to his name from eight starts. Winning claims. JUST A PIRATE (2) doesn't win out of turn but recent form sound. Finished second (23.07) at Gawler last time making it two minors on end. Good beginner aided by a nice draw. Expected to feature. VICTA HOWARD (8) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing sixth (31.95) in a Special conditions race at Gawler. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Key runner who gets his chance to atone. BUFFY'S NO ANGEL (6) is not to be discarded.",
